          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>1 parchment folio; Qurʾānic Text: Q 19:72-98; 18/19 lines per page; Dimensions: 335mm x 310mm; Script style: kūfī, type B.Ia; Estimated date of production: 660-710 (??).</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>This folio has been sold by the auction house N<ref target="https://www.nabecor.fr/2019/11/21/lest-republicain-parle-de-nabecor-encheres/">abecor in Nancy (France) </ref>on November 16th 2019 for the price <ref target="https://www.estrepublicain.fr/edition-de-nancy-ville/2019/11/21/une-page-du-coran-adjugee-114-000-a-nancy">of 114.000 EUR (140.000 EUR frais compris)</ref>. The page seems to belong to a codex to which have belonged the following fragments: BNF <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/en/manuscripts/32/page/1r?sura=2&amp;amp;verse=125">Arabe 331</ref>, and the Saint Petersburg <ref target="http://corpuscoranicum.de/handschriften/index/sure/4/vers/92?handschrift=331">Marcel 3</ref> (26 fol.), two fragments <ref target="https://www.corpuscoranicum.de/handschriften/index/sure/16/vers/96/handschrift/368">Leiden, Cod.or. 14.545b</ref> (1 fol.) and <ref target="https://www.corpuscoranicum.de/handschriften/index/sure/63/vers/1/handschrift/369">Leiden, Cod.or. 14.545c</ref> (1 fol.), Chicago <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/handschriften/index/sure/68/vers/9?handschrift=16">A 6959</ref> and <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/handschriften/index/sure/97/vers/3?handschrift=17">A 6990</ref> and possibly <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/handschriften/index/sure/11/vers/48?handschrift=886">E 16264 R</ref> (Pennsylvania University Museums, Philadelphia). </p>
              <p> </p>
              <p><ref target="https://www.interencheres.com/meubles-objets-art/belle-vente-mobiliere-260807/lot-22250292.html">According to the auction house Nabécor</ref> (the link is unfortunately no longer connected to the initial content), the fragment had been purchased around 1960 from the Drouot (Paris).  </p>
            </summary>
